HEADWORD: Scapula
<hw>Scap"u*la</hw> <pr>(sk⟦acr⟧p"⟦usl⟧*l⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> L. <plw>Scapulae</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, E.
<plw>Scapulas</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The principal bone of the shoulder girdle in
mammals; the shoulder blade.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the plates from which the
arms of a crinoid arise.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scapular</ent>⟦br⟧
